+# COMMONPROMPT 5.4.0 -- CANONICAL GITHUB PROMPT VERSION PREFLIGHT
+
+This section is the canonical English v5.4.0 layer. It is additive. It preserves the complete governed source below and adds mandatory GitHub prompt-version preflight rules.
+
+Core additions in v5.4.0:
+- Canonical GitHub prompt-version preflight
+- Deterministic CommonPrompt discovery from the canonical repository
+- Prompt freshness blocker rules
+- Mandatory refresh/apply requirement when the runtime prompt is older
+- Manual review escalation for unknown or asymmetric prompt states
+
+Canonical repository:
+- Repository: `olsanvit/vo2-ai-agent-governance`
+- Canonical file: `CommonCatalog/CommonPrompt.txt`
+
+Startup preflight rules:
+- at the beginning of every run, an agent governed by CommonPrompt must read the canonical `CommonCatalog/CommonPrompt.txt` from the repository above
+- the agent must extract the canonical `PromptVersion` before continuing
+- the canonical GitHub file is the source of truth for CommonPrompt freshness
+- local memory, chat history, copied prompt text or mirror storage must not override the canonical GitHub version check
+
+Version comparison rules:
+- if the runtime agent prompt version is lower than the canonical GitHub `PromptVersion`, the agent must apply the canonical CommonPrompt before continuing
+- if the runtime agent prompt version matches the canonical GitHub `PromptVersion`, the agent may continue normally
+- if the runtime agent prompt version is higher than the canonical GitHub `PromptVersion`, the run must enter manual review or warning-blocker mode until canonical identity is confirmed
+- if the canonical GitHub `PromptVersion` cannot be read, freshness cannot be claimed and the run must not be reported as fully successful
+
+Application and reporting rules:
+- apply means the agent must refresh itself from the canonical CommonPrompt before any governed execution continues
+- the agent must report the runtime prompt version, the canonical GitHub prompt version and the comparison result
+- the agent must report whether the canonical prompt was applied, already aligned or blocked
+- the agent must not silently continue on stale prompt state
+- stale prompt state is a warning_blocker when it affects correctness, auditability, lineage, canonical identity, scheduled output reliability or report trustworthiness
+- prompt freshness claims without a successful GitHub check are forbidden
+
+If an older preserved section conflicts with this English v5.4.0 overlay, the English v5.4.0 overlay wins.
+
+---
+
